# Air Pollution Analyzer using AT89C51 & PPD42NS Sensor

#Project Overview
The Air Pollution Analyzer is an embedded system designed to monitor dust concentration in the surrounding air using the AT89C51 microcontroller and PPD42NS dust sensor.
The system continuously measures airborne dust particles, classifies air quality into Low, Medium, or High levels, and displays the result on a 16×2 LCD. The project was designed and tested using Proteus Design Suite.


#Objectives
- Monitor air quality in real time
- Measure dust concentration using PPD42NS sensor
- Classify air quality as Low, Medium, or High
- Display results on a 16×2 LCD
- Develop a low-cost embedded monitoring system

